 ;; =====================================================================
 ;; THE PROMOTION LOOP (equity loop equivalent)
 ;; =====================================================================

 :promotion-loop
 {:description "work → cleanup evidence → candidate invariant → promotion → operational enforcement → prevented failures → cleaner work"
  :steps
  [{:id :PL-work       :name "Work happens"          :note "Live coding, missions, proofs"}
   {:id :PL-cleanup    :name "Cleanup reveals debt"   :note "Stash archaeology, root clutter, wrong-repo artifacts"}
   {:id :PL-candidate  :name "Pressure becomes candidate" :note "Recurring pattern earns a family entry"}
   {:id :PL-promotion  :name "Candidate promoted"    :note "Exemplar reaches operational strength; logic-layer extraction"}
   {:id :PL-enforce    :name "Operational enforcement" :note "The invariant bites on the live path"}
   {:id :PL-prevent    :name "Failures prevented"    :note "The class of mess that prompted cleanup no longer recurs"}
   {:id :PL-cleaner    :name "Cleaner work"          :note "Subtler invariant pressure emerges; cycle repeats at higher level"}]}

 ;; =====================================================================
 ;; GOVERNANCE QUESTIONS (equivalent of UKRN conversation prompts)
 ;; =====================================================================

 :governance-questions
 [{:id :Q1 :text "Should atomic-inspectable-units become always-on?"
   :family :F-atomic-inspectable-units :note "Currently bypassable"}
  {:id :Q2 :text "Should every session carry a canonical home-repo?"
   :family :F-peripheral-custody}
  {:id :Q3 :text "Should cleanup conditions become structural-law checks?"
   :family :F-archaeology-control :note "Or remain hygiene folklore?"}
  {:id :Q4 :text "Should peripheral stops normalize to explicit check-in outcomes?"
   :family :F-peripheral-custody}
  {:id :Q5 :text "Which candidates deserve promotion to foundational always-on?"
   :family nil :note "The meta-governance question"}]

 ;; =====================================================================
 ;; COMPARATIVE DIAGNOSIS
 ;; =====================================================================

 :comparative
 {:ukrn-parallel
  {:I0 {:futon "9 operational invariants in futon1a. Firm substrate."
        :ukrn  "Training delivery exists. Untested downstream."
        :feel  "futon I0 is solid. UKRN I0 is claimed but unproven."}
   :I1 {:futon "7 operational invariants across futon3b/3c. Phase ordering, status, existence."
        :ukrn  "Exit interviews don't exist yet. Optional forms yield nothing."
        :feel  "futon I1 is operational. UKRN I1 is absent."}
   :I2 {:futon "Mixed: graph-symmetry operational, failure-locality strong in some repos, candidate elsewhere."
        :ukrn  "Evidence sharing doesn't exist."
        :feel  "futon I2 is partially operational. UKRN I2 is absent."}
   :I3 {:futon "Mixed: required-outputs operational, atomic-inspectable-units bypassable, repo-role-clarity no exemplar."
        :ukrn  "Materials workshop nominal, mentoring and curriculum absent."
        :feel  "futon I3 has real operational pieces but gaps. UKRN I3 is mostly absent."}
   :I4 {:futon "All candidate. Peripheral custody, budgeted action, archaeology, cross-store: no operational exemplar."
        :ukrn  "All absent. Governance, recognition, pulse check: proposed but not built."
        :feel  "Both I4 layers are the frontier. Neither system governs itself yet."}}

  :why-futon-feels-better
  "The futon stack has a solid substrate (I0, I1 operational) and the promotion loop
   is visibly working: cleanup reveals pressure, pressure becomes candidates, some
   candidates have already been promoted. The system is learning about itself.

   UKRN has a claimed I0 with no detection mechanism, so it can't even tell whether
   its core fact holds. The promotion loop hasn't started because there's no evidence
   to promote from. The spreadsheet is a list of tasks without a model of how they
   relate — which is exactly the folklore-over-evidence pattern that the futon stack's
   human-visible-inspectability family is designed to prevent."

  :what-they-share
  "Both systems have an I4 frontier that is entirely candidate/absent. Neither system
   governs itself yet. The difference is that the futon stack knows this about itself
   (it has an inventory that names the gap), while UKRN doesn't (it has a spreadsheet
   that doesn't know what it's missing)."}}
